  "prompt": "What is the weirdest question you have ever been asked in an interview?",
  "response": "Interviews can sometimes take unexpected turns, and sometimes candidates or interviewers ask questions that are downright bizarre. One of the weirdest questions I\u2019ve come across is:  \n\n**\"If you were a fruit, what fruit would you be and why?\"**  \n\nThis question is odd because it seems completely unrelated to job performance or professional skills. However, it\u2019s often used to gauge creativity, self-awareness, and how well a candidate can think on their feet.  \n\nAnother strange one I\u2019ve heard is: **\"How would you survive a zombie apocalypse?\"** While this might seem like a joke, it can be a way to assess problem-solving skills, teamwork, and strategic thinking in an unconventional scenario.  \n\nWeird questions like these are often designed to throw candidates off balance and see how they handle unexpected or unconventional situations. They can also reveal personality traits or thought processes that might not come out in more traditional interview questions.  \n\nHave you ever been asked something strange in an interview?",
  "temperature": 1.0,
